(thirdQuint)Safety of a Booster Dose of GlaxoSmithKline (GSK) Biologicals' Boostrix Vaccine in Healthy Vietnamese Children.

 A phase III, single-group, open-label study of GSK Biologicals' vaccine BoostrixTM administered as a booster vaccine dose in healthy Vietnamese children aged 6-10 years.

 A single booster dose of BoostrixTM will be administered at Visit 1 (Day 0) and subjects will be observed until Visit 2 (Day 30).

 Safety will be assessed in terms of solicited adverse events (during 4 days post vaccination), unsolicited adverse events (during 31 days post vaccination) and serious adverse event (during the trial period).

 This protocol summary was updated following an administrative change of adding the EudraCT number to this study.

