This study will evaluate the safety and reactogenicity of GSK Biologicals' combined reduced-antigen-content diphtheria-tetanus-acellular pertussis (dTpa) vaccine, Boostrix cent when given as a single injection to 6-10 year old children.

 Data that are available globally on the age group from four to six years of age will be used to bridge the age gap in this study and aid in the registration of the vaccine for children from the age of four years.

